1) For +, -, *, and print operations, only "int" and "string" are permissable types More over, both operands must be of the same type.

2) For any assignment statement, the left-hand side and the right hand side must be of the same type.

3) For any method invocation, the return type must agree with the declared method type.

4) The number of parameters and their types must agree between the method declaration and the method invocation.

5) Every identifier (including class field identifier) which appear in the expressions must be declared in an appropriate scope.

6) Exactly one method named "main" must be declared in one of the classes. Its type must be "int".

